name: "SOLD"   Iida 233 Tenor 4-String Banjo
description:
Sorry this one just sold 5-6-13... but Check back often!!

“Vintage” Iida 233 Model 4-String Tenor Banjo

These 1970’s Banjo’s were made in Japan by true craftsmen of the day and were in direct competition with the Gibson banjo’s and matched or copied there style so closely that eventually lead to law-suits.

Some features (as described in their 1978 catalog) include: Tube and Flange construction, Flathead Cast tone ring, 24 brackets, Geared 5th string peg, Planetary tuning pegs, Pearloid buttons, trap door (clamshell) tailpiece, Bow tie inlay pattern and inlaid mahogany resonator.

This Iida 233 model is an example of a very nice and well kept banjo and comes with a chip board case, new D’Addario strings and a Strap.

A 1979 retail price list shows this banjo at $629.50. We are asking $550.00 OBO. Please look at all the pictures provided and feel free to CONTACT US with any questions you may have. I will ship only to the 48 Contiguous States or Local shopping is always available in the Kansas City Metro area!
